  Let X_0 be a scheme of finite type over the field k, and suppose that X_0 is simple (by which we mean absolutely simple) over k, but not necessarily proper over k.
  Let A be a local Artinian ring with residue field k.
  We are interested in finding schemes X that are flat over A, and such that X \otimes _A k=X_0 (this is the starting point of the "_theory of modules_", or of "structure variations" of X_0).

